OL,6,FThe UN Convention on the Rights of a
OL,7,FChild says governments which have
OL,8,Fsigned it should ensure that "neither
OL,9,Fcapital punishment nor life
OL,10,Fimprisonment without possibility of
OL,11,Frelease shall be imposed for offences
OL,12,Fcommitted by persons below 18 years of
OL,13,Fage".
OL,15,FHealey told ITV News: "It's important
OL,16,Fto note that the scope for the court
OL,17,Fto impose a whole life sentence is
OL,18,Frestricted by the age threshold.
