OL,6,FMinisters have no plans to bring back
OL,7,Fcapital punishment, Downing Street
OL,8,Fsaid, citing Parliament consistently
OL,9,Fvoting against it being restored in
OL,10,Frecent decades.
OL,12,FA No 10 spokesman also told reporters
OL,13,Fthey hoped the public inquiry into the
OL,14,FSouthport stabbings will move "as
OL,15,Fquickly as time allows".
OL,17,FTimetables and terms of reference will
OL,18,Fbe set out once the government has
OL,19,Fconsulted the coroner and given
OL,20,Ffamilies the opportunity to comment,
OL,21,Fhe said.
